quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  4,66,"Had We prescribed for them, [commanding]: ‘Slay [the guilty among] your folks or leave your habitations,’ they would not have done it except a few of them. And if they had done as they were advised, it would have been better for them and stronger in confirming [their faith]"
  4,67,Then We would surely have given them from Us a great reward
  4,68,and We would have guided them to a straight path
  4,69,"Whoever obeys Allah and the Apostle—they are with those whom Allah has blessed, including the prophets and the truthful, the martyrs and the righteous, and excellent companions are they"
  4,70,"That is the grace of Allah, and Allah suffices as knower [of His creatures]"
  4,71,"O you who have faith! Take your precautions, then go forth in companies, or go forth en masse"
  4,72,"Among you is indeed he who drags his feet, and should an affliction visit you, he says, ‘It was certainly Allah’s blessing that I did not accompany them!’"
  4,73,"But should a bounty from Allah come to you, he will say—as if there were no [tie of friendship and] affection between you and him—‘I wish I were with them so that I had achieved a great success!’"
  4,74,"Let those who sell the life of this world for the Hereafter fight in the way of Allah; and whoever fights in the way of Allah, and then is slain, or he subdues [the enemy], We shall soon give him a great reward"